# 🐱🐶 Cat vs Dog Classifier using SVM

A simple Machine Learning project that classifies images of cats and dogs using **Support Vector Machines (SVM)**.

---

## 📁 Dataset

- Source: [Kaggle Dogs vs Cats](https://www.kaggle.com/c/dogs-vs-cats/data)
- Total Images Used:
  - Cats: 10,000
  - Dogs: 10,000

---

## ⚙️ Features

- Preprocessing using OpenCV (`cv2`)
- Image resized to **64x64** and flattened
- Balanced dataset using random undersampling
- Trained using **Linear SVM**
- Validation accuracy printed during training

---

## 🧠 Model Performance

- ✅ Total Images Loaded: 20,000
- 🎯 Validation Accuracy: **~93%**
- 📦 Trained Model: `svm_model.pkl` (saved in `model/` folder)

---

## 📤 Output

All output files and results are saved in the [`outputs/`](outputs/) folder:
- `training_output.txt`: Training log with accuracy
- `prediction_output.txt`: Prediction results on test images
- `screenshots/`: Terminal screenshots of model run

